# FTP Client

FTP is a client-server protocol to transfer files to or from the servers. An FTP client sends FTP request messages to an FTP server. FTP server interprets the request message, takes appropriate action, and sends back response message to the client.

Here implemented is the client-side of FTP.


## Technologies
This application has been developed using C programming language. CMake utility is necessary
to build as well as to run the unit test of this application.

To perform unit test of this application GCC compiler must have CMake and CTest. This application has been tested on Debian 4.9 (Linux) with 
GCC 6.3.0.


## Build, Run, Test, Installation, and Uninstallation

Type following at the command prompt to clean previously built artefacts of the assignment:
make clean

Type following at the command prompt to build the application from your own source code:
make

Type the following command to run the example server provided
make run-example-server

Type the following to run the client you made and connect to the server 
make run-client

From here you are free to use the FTP protocol in any way desired.


To test the full program program type:
make test


## Usage

This program is designed to perform various FTP operations using the main function, which interacts with the FTP server based on user input. The program includes functions for basic FTP tasks such as connecting to the server, uploading and downloading files, listing directory contents, and moving between them.


